text:
[2024/05/03 12:00:00 GMT+0000] [00:44:05] Participant 34: Handled the sale of the bar when Nick bought it in 2005, so it was Louie Lavelle, the father opened it in 1957. Very involved around the town, women's choir, billiards club, Brown County hiking club, last person to leave the bar the night Nick died, left maybe an hour before closing. Well, last person to leave the bar, we assume Carmen was there. 
[00:44:30] Participant 35: Yeah. [00:44:31] Participant 34: So, last patron to leave the bar. 
[00:44:34] Participant 36: Yeah. [00:44:36] Participant 34: She seemed on edge, but when I asked if everything was okay, she shrugged it off, left a note on her menu, and a matchbox on the counter for Nick. So, the menu is… 
[00:44:45] Participant 36: The menu is here. 
[00:44:48] Participant 34: Yeah, it says, we need to talk, and it's highlighted Wednesday, about land, about Devil's Well, either land or…no, Wednesday about Devil's Well, land or and, 11 p.m. 
[00:45:04] Participant 35: Okay. [00:45:04] Researcher 2: We are at 45 minutes, so that's half time. [00:45:04] Participant 36: Okay. [00:45:06] Participant 35: We are getting there. 
[00:45:09] Participant 36: Yeah, we're getting there. 
[00:45:15] Participant 34: And she talked about the Old Scratch Tavern, and everyone could see what a special place Nick had made it. Looked like she'd been crying, when we talked afterwards, and then she said something really odd like, if only I had been faster, maybe I could have made a difference. Before I could ask her what she meant, Nolan came over, and she started telling her about a job opening for a fry cook at Lonesome Diner. He was grateful for the lead, we've all been struggling to find work since the Old Scratch closed, it's hard to believe we'll ever find another job as great. She said she'd been having a rough time that night, she was preoccupied with some work problems, and had decided to go for a drive, try and clear my thoughts from there. And then when he asked her about the stuff she left at the bar, she said, we shouldn't talk here, hustled me out of the house in a hurry, tried to call her, no answer. Called her office, said she'd left on a business trip, not sure when she was to get back. So, Donna, well did she have the opportunity, yes… 
[00:46:23] Participant 36: Yes, Donna. 
[00:46:28] Participant 34: …to go and kill Nick. She also left him a note, but she's left him a note saying we need to talk on…let's see.
